.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" I think it might need to match the constructor exactly. I should look into how Java beans use Expression to target new class values with arguments since it can instantiate classes. For nested public static classes, I'll keep in mind that the constructor needs to be public. I might just need to use strings for constructor choices and asserts without directly using reflection.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Considering test classes**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI'm thinking about whether to write a new file or edit an existing one. If a top-level test class is package-private, it might violate the rule that states all top-level test classes must be public. The new file will be public, which is good. But what's the point of editing the existing one? I should think about keeping the placeholder, maybe making it public, but I definitely need to create the ClassUtilsTest file, since I'll ensure there's a mapping between report classes and test classes.\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"toolCall\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_hECum4b1WlAnVlJyma9KOg1o|fc_01874e31d905f86f0169f691553320819cb918175efa758e71\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"write\\\", \\\"arguments\\\": {\\\"path\\\": \\\"tests/src/org.flywaydb/flyway-core/10.0.0/src/test/java/org_flywaydb/flyway_core/ClassUtilsTest.java\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"/*\\\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\\\n *\\\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\\\n */\\\\npackage org_flywaydb.flyway_core;\\\\n\\\\nimport org.flywaydb.core.internal.util.ClassUtils;\\\\nimport org.flywaydb.core.internal.util.ClassUtils.DoNotMapForLogging;\\\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\\\n\\\\nimport java.util.Map;\\\\n\\\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\\\n\\\\npublic class ClassUtilsTest {\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void instantiatesClassesByNameAndClassLiteral() {\\\\n        ClassLoader classLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\\\\n\\\\n        DefaultConstructed defaultConstructed = ClassUtils.instantiate(DefaultConstructed.class.getName(), classLoader);\\\\n        DefaultConstructed constructedFromClass = ClassUtils.instantiate(DefaultConstructed.class);\\\\n        ConstructedWithArguments constructedWithArguments = ClassUtils.instantiate(\\\\n                ConstructedWithArguments.class.getName(),\\\\n                classLoader,\\\\n                \\\\\\\"flyway\\\\\\\",\\\\n                10);\\\\n\\\\n        assertThat(defaultConstructed.getValue()).isEqualTo(\\\\\\\"default\\\\\\\");\\\\n        assertThat(constructedFromClass.getValue()).isEqualTo(\\\\\\\"default\\\\\\\");\\\\n        assertThat(constructedWithArguments.getDescription()).isEqualTo(\\\\\\\"flyway-10\\\\\\\");\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void detectsAndLoadsConcreteImplementationClasses() throws Exception {\\\\n        ClassLoader classLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\\\\n\\\\n        assertThat(ClassUtils.isPresent(DefaultConstructed.class.getName(), classLoader)).isTrue();\\\\n        assertThat(ClassUtils.isImplementationPresent(TestService.class.getName(), classLoader)).isFalse();\\\\n\\\\n        Class<? extends TestService> loadedClass = ClassUtils.loadClass(\\\\n                TestService.class,\\\\n                TestServiceImplementation.class.getName(),\\\\n                classLoader);\\\\n\\\\n        assertThat(loadedClass).isEqualTo(TestServiceImplementation.class);\\\\n        assertThat(ClassUtils.loadClass(TestService.class, String.class.getName(), classLoader)).isNull();\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void readsStaticAndInstanceFieldValues() {\\\\n        assertThat(ClassUtils.getStaticFieldValue(\\\\n                FieldFixture.class.getName(),\\\\n                \\\\\\\"PUBLIC_STATIC_VALUE\\\\\\\",\\\\n                Thread.currentThread().get