ed public static classes, I'll keep in mind that the constructor needs to be public. I might just need to use strings for constructor choices and asserts without directly using reflection.\\\\n\\\\n**Considering test classes**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about whether to write a new file or edit an existing one. If a top-level test class is package-private, it might violate the rule that states all top-level test classes must be public. The new file will be public, which is good. But what's the point of editing the existing one? I should think about keeping the placeholder, maybe making it public, but I definitely need to create the ClassUtilsTest file, since I'll ensure there's a mapping between report classes and test classes.\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_01874e31d905f86f0169f691400acc819c8ad5afcca953dff9\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp9pFVh-L90jFWf8_QmxJW6jjOKJy-yDPIt15npLwAadqaCCThWYY9dUzxFbiwBwBWdGNCfg0Yuybk_w_6MCgxRjqlNvo0Ie8MJlsIkVH2H3tIT-0pLWrOSPEbTOw1CkCxNO8j1RUNt1slAeGlukOYdM-5RtkqE3tX8bbm_oGX4GBUmdeHZkUHORk_3CAyRMovJoDooxq-IU0HdSMHs4w6rByz9CUOohot2gQ0AdDHfdYknXMMVfaYyiPvKzaSdDFWBQqdxL0ApyyKeBh0BF3R51XdkrPZK2FkGIXAgege5FC1mAsX39Zl89OEZvz3M7oYZ-SgEuGgmVY0uUC6rYewNdY36y0eQCxd895_juevUSxb3jyVIi0e7guGw_-jKcbhUh6zjf3W3aiEtnzYDC6iHQSoD6M1OlgZUxOjICnP35qjhroZCar4o9UutB06PjA-MogzP62ROd9IgCS_BOAovI8Dfo4LaF-rolinczULIfcYacopYnSoTfM-9n5eNOY2GU7r9pCeITQJ0J5U_pNkxX5Cp3RdQPklb-h7ZmX4YLGpxQQJIUuKDm8gN20dRg9f92A4VRbzQVPaTTivlxcGXCVi8kXYLlbzjfZlKQ8dEQwefwSC55eom3_lZvUqFONrRt1q5FV7ERhLYEZMkhfcgqtP_QL0P-m8KRLozc0_4x9E5WPsi5hYLJyFoa3B5yHMJyizJTPpg_VCMlKN2MkCrBDV74F_ChOyME0DJD2gn9BdEwu0x4KeJX0ZU3Jv-TnWxupDFiiqcyyfdGi4YelvAkhutvAi1n5xjeEHoMi7KB-1ai_5PXe6DYp1q2qsGKD_7dqyRWI3JBEmNztSwzT6E20osf4kxgyxLiO_lbUFDXcbAaX51cazck49Clz7aszVFvTbFsiiA9XDTubIeqCU6OTpd4B1IQqYqWwjxt7MBDHnDmw8MPPOTG4ZZvdTFrHBpfDZaR1O5kxmBe9UN3rjUI000XFcb_idpEI1vSzESrGvseQpcd98PjpKBBQ-6tFR3iTOtr6Rce6OOmlS4YNe